sequenceDiagram
    participant User as External User
    participant Gateway as Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+ Terminate
    participant EnvoyFilter as EnvoyFilter<br/>ext_authz + Lua
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service-ca)
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth /<br/>OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Component as Component Backend<br/>(HTTPRoute target)

    Note over User,Component: Flow 1: User Request → Component via Gateway API

    User->>Gateway: HTTPS/443 Request<br/>TLS 1.2+ (terminate)
    Gateway->>EnvoyFilter: ext_authz check<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    EnvoyFilter->>AuthProxy: Forward for auth<br/>8443/TCP TLS (service-ca)
    AuthProxy->>OAuth: OAuth2/OIDC validation<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    OAuth-->>AuthProxy: Auth response + tokens
    AuthProxy-->>EnvoyFilter: Auth OK + user info
    Note over EnvoyFilter: Lua script strips OAuth cookies,<br/>injects Bearer token in<br/>Authorization header
    EnvoyFilter->>Component: Forward request<br/>Bearer Token injected
    Component-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller
    participant Manifests as Manifest Engine<br/>(Kustomize/Helm)

    Note over User,Manifests: Flow 2: DSC Reconciliation → Component Deployment

    User->>K8sAPI: Create/Update DSC CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>RBAC auth
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validation + Defaulting<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (cert-manager)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admitted (validated)
    K8sAPI-->>DSCCtrl: Watch event (DSC changed)
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Component CRs<br/>(Dashboard, KServe, etc.)<br/>6443/TCP ServiceAccount
    K8sAPI-->>CompCtrl: Watch event (Component CR)
    CompCtrl->>Manifests: Render manifests<br/>(local, in-process)
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy resources<br/>(Deployments, Services, etc.)<br/>6443/TCP ServiceAccount

    participant OTel as OpenTelemetry<br/>Collector
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(MonitoringStack)
    participant Thanos as Thanos Querier<br/>10902/TCP
    participant Perses as Perses<br/>Dashboard

    Note over OTel,Perses: Flow 3: Monitoring Stack Data Collection

    OTel->>Component: Scrape metrics<br/>varies HTTP/HTTPS<br/>ServiceAccount
    OTel->>Prometheus: Push via OTLP<br/>HTTP TLS (webTLSConfig)<br/>Bearer Token
    Prometheus->>Thanos: Federation<br/>10902/TCP HTTP<br/>In-cluster
    Perses->>Thanos: Query metrics<br/>9091/9092 HTTPS<br/>TLS (CA ConfigMap)<br/>Bearer Token
